-- Argentina Stocks: Siderar SAIC, Telecom Argentina Increase
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-02-01T18:08:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/argentina-stocks-siderar-saic-telecom-argentina-increase.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 3:06 p.m. in  Buenos
Aires .  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index increased 1.8 percent to 2,837.52.  Argentine stocks rose in line with global equities after
U.S. manufacturing grew at the fastest pace since June.  China ’s
manufacturing output unexpectedly rose.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)  ,  Argentina ’s largest steelmaker,
advanced 6.1 percent to 25.30 pesos and was on track for its
biggest gain since Nov. 30.  Telecom Argentina SA (TECO2)  (TECO2 AF), the Argentine telephone
operator, rose 3.9 percent to 20.15 pesos. Cell phone calls
nationwide increased 24.9 percent in December compared to the
same month a year earlier, the national statistics institute
reported yesterday in a release on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
